Dana Air has decorated new captains on its Boeing 737 aircraft and other aircraft in its fleet, assuring its staff that it will continue to reward excellence and hard work. Decorating Captain Shina Agbelese and Captain Ademola Akinyemi in Lagos, the Chief Operating Officer of Dana Air, Mr Obi Mbanuzuo, said young Nigerian pilots are performing excellently, and doing amazingly well. Dana Air also announced that all its pilots, cabin crew and ground staff have all been vaccinated while that of its backend staff is ongoing in Lagos. The Media and Communications Manager of Dana Air, Kingsley Ezenwa said, “all our pilots, cabin crew and ground staff have concluded their vaccination while that of our backend staff is ongoing.”